# How did the Ukrainian government respond to the attack on Russian missile in Dnipro?

## Summary
The Ukrainian government responded to the Russian missile attack on Dnipro by deploying air defense systems to shot down 21 of the 33 missiles.1 Additionally, the U.S. and Germany offered to send Bradley fighting vehicles and Marder armored personnel carriers respectively.2 Unfortunately, the Armed Forces of Ukraine lacked the firepower capabilities to shoot down the missiles.3 As a result, 12 people were killed in the attack and rescue teams were sent in to search for survivors.4 President Volodymyr Zelenskiy declared that the rescue operation would continue as long as there was a chance of saving lives.5

